From: Gilly <gilroyscott1970@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 25 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +1000
Subject: net: phy: rtl8261n: fix IRQ race on Airoha AN7581

Two timing problems cause IRQ lines for the RTL8261N/RTL8264B to be
permanently disabled ("nobody cared") on the Airoha AN7581 platform,
leaving phylib to fall back to polling (irq=POLL) on ~40-60% of boots:

1. probe() to phy_attach_direct() window: VEND2:INER is at its hardware
   default of 0xf3f0 at probe time. Any autoneg or link event between
   probe() and phy_request_interrupt() fires with no handler registered
   and the kernel disables the IRQ permanently.

2. Soft reset in config_init() restores VEND2:INER to 0xf3f0. A link-down
   event fires within milliseconds of reset deassert -- well within the
   mandatory 30 ms settle period -- before any INER mask write can occur.

Fix both windows:
- Mask VEND2:INER to 0 at end of rtl826xb_probe() (closes window 1).
- Mask VEND2:INER to 0 immediately after reset deassert in
  rtkphy_config_init(), before the 30 ms settle (closes window 2).
- phylib re-enables INER bits once phy_request_interrupt() has registered
  the handler.

Note: this is the AN7581 + in-tree rtl8261n driver (Linux 6.12) backport
of the original IRQ-race fix posted against the new upstream-friendly
realtek_main.c driver in openwrt PR #22563:
https://github.com/openwrt/openwrt/pull/22563

Original-author: Gilly1970 <gilroyscott1970@gmail.com>
Backport-from: Gilly1970/Gemtek-W1700K@f992bfd70c
[ rchen14b: adapt to the in-tree rtl8261n driver paths
  (drivers/net/phy/rtl8261n/rtk_phy.c) and the 6.12 kernel; the firmware
  load / EPROBE_DEFER half of the original patch is omitted because our
  driver loads its patch DB synchronously from a built-in table, not
  from request_firmware_direct(), so window 1 from the upstream patch
  does not apply here. ]
Signed-off-by: Ryan Chen <rchen14b@gmail.com>
---
--- a/drivers/net/phy/rtl8261n/rtk_phy.c
+++ b/drivers/net/phy/rtl8261n/rtk_phy.c
@@ -65,6 +65,16 @@ static int rtl826xb_probe(struct phy_dev
     priv->pnswap_tx = device_property_read_bool(dev, "realtek,pnswap-tx");
     phydev->priv = priv;
 
+    /* Mask VEND2:INER at probe: on Airoha AN7581 the IRQ mux assigns a
+     * live IRQ line to this PHY before phy_request_interrupt() registers
+     * a handler. If INER is left at its hardware default (0xf3f0), the
+     * first link change fires an interrupt with no handler, the kernel
+     * marks the line "nobody cared" and disables it permanently for the
+     * session. rtkphy_config_init() re-masks after soft reset; phylib
+     * re-enables INER bits once the handler is registered.
+     */
+    phy_write_mmd(phydev, MDIO_MMD_VEND2, 0xA424, 0);
+
     return 0;
 }
 
@@ -83,6 +93,12 @@ static int rtkphy_config_init(struct phy
             phy_modify_mmd_changed(phydev, 30, 0x145, BIT(0)  , 1);
             mdelay(30);
             phy_modify_mmd_changed(phydev, 30, 0x145, BIT(0)  , 0);
+            /* Soft reset restores VEND2:INER to its hardware default;
+             * mask immediately after deassert. The link-down event fires
+             * within milliseconds of reset deassert, well within the
+             * mandatory 30 ms settle period, so the mask must precede
+             * the settle delay. */
+            phy_write_mmd(phydev, MDIO_MMD_VEND2, 0xA424, 0);
             mdelay(30);
           #endif
 
